        "message": "LU-19986 build: Avoid typedef unsigned int bool\n\nInstead include the header to ensure bool is available:\n\nThe resolves a build failure:\n...\nlutf_global_wrap.c:3238:22: error: bool cannot be defined via typedef\n 3238 | typedef unsigned int bool;\n      |                      ^~~~\nlutf_global_wrap.c:3238:22: note: 'bool' is a keyword with '-std=c23'\n...\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-13285\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Shaun Tancheff <shaun.tancheff@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: I4dba3ca1d219f9e64edc72c2965974efa86a7c8c\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/64569\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nReviewed-by: Chris Horn <chris.horn@hpe.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\n"
